ddl.statement: CREATE TABLE test.public.users (id INTEGER, name VARCHAR(255), email VARCHAR(255), created_at TIMESTAMP)
CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS test.optimized

CREATE TABLE test.optimized.users (
  id INTEGER,
  name VARCHAR(255),
  email VARCHAR(255),
  created_at TIMESTAMP
) WITH (
  format = 'ICEBERG',
  partitioning = ARRAY['created_at'],
  clustering = ARRAY['id'],
  'write.compression-codec' = 'ZSTD',
  'write.target-file-size-bytes' = '268435456',
  'read.vectorization.enabled' = 'true',
  'write.parquet.compression-codec' = 'ZSTD',
  'write.parquet.page-size-bytes' = '1048576',
  'write.parquet.row-group-size-bytes' = '134217728'
)

migrations.statement: INSERT INTO test.optimized.users SELECT id, name, email, created_at FROM test.public.users
SELECT COUNT(*) as validation FROM test.optimized.users

queries.query:
SELECT * FROM test.optimized.users WHERE id = 1
LIMIT 10000;
